{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12443: Setting ATTR_ENUMERATED_COERCION compat to false does not disable warning",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:41.616572+00:00",
  "text": "Setting ATTR_ENUMERATED_COERCION compat to false does not disable warning\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.13\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/6nqevc2y/\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nRun the fiddle\n\n### What is expected?\n\nNo ATTR_ENUMERATED_COERCION warning should be logged to the console.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nATTR_ENUMERATED_COERCION warning is logged to the console.\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: v2 compat",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
